Articles

   OpenGL articles (non-tutorials)
     * [https://github.com/LWJGL/lwjgl3-wiki/wiki/2.6.1.-Ray-tracing-with-
       OpenGL-Compute-Shaders-%28Part-I%29](2014) Ray tracing with OpenGL
       Compute Shaders by Kai Burjack - Detailed tutorial series about ray
       tracing using OpenGL (LWJGL).
     * [http://richg42.blogspot.com.au/2014/05/things-that-drive-me-nuts-a
       bout-opengl.html](2014) Things that drive me nuts about OpenGL by
       Rich Geldreich - Constructive (or not) criticism of GL API.
     * [https://fgiesen.wordpress.com/2011/07/09/a-trip-through-the-graphi
       cs-pipeline-2011-index](2011) A trip through the graphics pipeline
       by Fabian Giesen - Compreheensive and rich series about the
       D3D/OpenGL graphics pipeline.
     * [http://duriansoftware.com/joe/An-intro-to-modern-OpenGL.-Chapter-1
       :-The-Graphics-Pipeline.html](2010) What is OpenGL? by Joe Groff -
       Brief introduction to the building blocks of OpenGL.

Books

   Popular books about OpenGL
     * [http://www.amazon.com/dp/1558603875]A Trip Down the Graphics
       Pipeline by Jim Blinn - Popular book that contains wealth
       information about the graphics pipeline, and of the best sources to
       learn the core concepts of Computer Graphics.
     * [http://www.amazon.com/dp/0321399528]Computer Graphics by John F.
       Hughes, et al. - Computer Graphics is indeed a must for anyone
       being involved in the design and implementation of Computer
       Graphics algorithms. However, this is not a OpenGL focused book,
       but contains valuable demonstrations of the technology.
     * [http://www.amazon.com/dp/0132545233]Interactive Computer Graphics
       by Edward Angel and Dave Shreiner - It provides several examples
       using OpenGL and it covers several aspects at once, but if you are
       trying to learn OpenGL on your own you might not find this helpful.
     * [http://www.amazon.com/dp/0321933885]OpenGL ES 3.0 Programming
       Guide by Dan Ginsburg, et al. - It presents all the necessary
       information to use the OpenGL ES 3.0 API in a clear manner.
     * [http://www.amazon.com/dp/1439893764]OpenGL Insights by Patrick
       Cozzi, Christophe Riccio - Rich and comprehensive resource to learn
       techniques and tips, covering several advanced topics of OpenGL.
     * [http://www.amazon.com/dp/0321773039]OpenGL Programming Guide by
       Dave Shreiner, et al. - It does a good job covering the basics and
       providing clear reference of the API.
     * [http://www.amazon.com/dp/0321637631]OpenGL Shading Language by
       Randi J. Rost, et al. - Very clear and well written book about
       Shading Language. Also, it provides several explanations of writing
       shaders.
     * [http://www.amazon.com/dp/0321712617]OpenGL SuperBible by Richard
       S. Wright, et al. - It covers the basic concepts of computer
       graphics and provides clear examples using OpenGL. Definitely, it
       is a must for beginners.
     * [http://www.amazon.com/dp/1568814240]Real-Time Rendering by Tomas
       Akenine-Moller, Eric Haines and Naty Hoffman - It does a good job
       at explaining concepts for game engine, basis for game client
       programming as well as the necessary knowledge for understanding
       DirectX and OpenGL.

Debug

   Debugging and profiling libraries
     * [http://apitrace.github.io/]apitrace - Tools for tracing OpenGL,
       Direct3D, and other graphics APIs.
     * [http://developer.amd.com/tools-and-sdks/opencl-zone/codexl/]CodeXL
       - AMD's OpenGL debugger and profiler. It's the most recent version
       of gDEBugger.
     * [http://glsl-debugger.github.io/]GL-SL Debugger - Tool for
       debugging OpenGL programs.
     * [https://github.com/dtrebilco/glintercept]GLIntercept - OpenGL
       function call interceptor for Windows.
     * [https://software.intel.com/en-us/gpa]Intel-GPA - Intel's OpenGL
       Graphics Performance Analyzer.
     * [https://developer.nvidia.com/nvidia-nsight-visual-studio-edition]N
       VIDIA® Nsight(TM) - Development platform for graphics applications.
     * [https://github.com/ValveSoftware/vogl]vogl - OpenGL capture and
       playback debugger developed by Valve.

GLSL Editors

   Online GLSL Editors
     * [http://glslsandbox.com/]GLSL Sandbox - Online live editor for
       fragment shaders.
     * [http://glslb.in/]GLSLbin - Fragment shader sandbox supporting
       [https://github.com/stackgl/glslify]glslify.
     * [http://shdr.bkcore.com/]SHDR Editor - Live GLSL shader editor,
       viewer and validator.
     * [https://www.shadertoy.com/]Shader Toy - Most popular live editor
       for fragment shaders.
     * [http://shaderfrog.com/]ShaderFrog - WebGL Shader Editor and
       Composer

Libraries

   Useful libraries for OpenGL applications
     * [http://assimp.sourceforge.net/]assimp - Portable library to import
       3D models in a uniform manner.
     * [http://bulletphysics.org/wordpress]Bullet - It provides state of
       the art collision detection, soft body and rigid body dynamics.
     * [http://freeglut.sourceforge.net/]freeGLUT - Mature library that
       allows to create/manage windows containing OpenGL contexts.
     * [http://www.glfw.org/]GLFW - Modern library for creating/interact
       windows with OpenGL contexts.
     * [https://github.com/brackeen/glfm]GLFM - Supplies an OpenGL ES
       context and input events for mobile devices and the web.
     * [http://glm.g-truc.net/0.9.6/index.html]glm - Mathematics library
       for graphics software based on the GLSL specifications.
     * [https://github.com/mosra/magnum]Magnum - It is a 2D/3D graphics
       engine for modern OpenGL.
     * [http://google.github.io/mathfu/]MathFu - C++ math library
       developed primarily for games focused on simplicity and efficiency.
     * [http://newtondynamics.com/forum/newton.php]Newton - It is a
       cross-platform life-like physics.
     * [http://oglplus.org/]OGLplus - Collection of libraries which
       implement an object-oriented facade over OpenGL.
     * [http://www.libsdl.org/]SDL - Designed to provide low level access
       to multimedia and graphics hardware.
     * [http://www.sfml-dev.org/]SFML - Simple interface to ease the
       development of games and multimedia applications.
     * [http://www.lonesock.net/soil.html]SOIL - Tiny C library used
       primarily for uploading textures into OpenGL. (see
       [https://bitbucket.org/SpartanJ/soil2]SOIL2)
     * [https://github.com/stevenlovegrove/Pangolin]Pangolin - Lightweight
       portable rapid development library for managing OpenGL display /
       interaction and abstracting video input.

Profile Loaders

   Profile loaders for OpenGL
     * [https://github.com/skaslev/gl3w]gl3w - Simple OpenGL core profile
       loader.
     * [https://github.com/Dav1dde/glad]glad - Multi profile
       loader-generator based on the official specs.
     * [https://github.com/nnesse/glbindify]glbindify - Commmand line tool
       to generate C bindings for OpenGL, wgl, and glX.
     * [https://github.com/cginternals/glbinding]glbinding - Profile
       loader leveraging C++11 features to provide type safety.
     * [http://glew.sourceforge.net/]GLEW - Mature cross-platform library
       to load OpenGL extensions.
     * [https://bitbucket.org/alfonse/glloadgen/wiki/Home]glLoadGen -
       Multi profile loader-generator written in Lua.

References

   OpenGL references
     * [http://docs.gl/]docs.GL - It is an alternative documentation for
       OpenGL.
     * [http://web.eecs.umich.edu/%7Esugih/courses/eecs487/common/notes/AP
       ITables.xml]OpenGL API Tables - Quick reference of API's for
       several OpenGL and GLSL versions.
     * [https://www.khronos.org/files/opengl43-quick-reference-card.pdf]Op
       enGL Cheat Sheet - Quick reference card of OpenGL 4.3 commands and
       syntax.
     * [https://www.opengl.org/sdk/docs]OpenGL Docs - Official
       documentation website.
     * [https://www.opengl.org/wiki/Main_Page]OpenGL Wiki - Official
       OpenGL wiki.

Talks

   OpenGL related talks
     * [http://gdcvault.com/play/1020791/]Approaching Zero Driver Overhead
       in OpenGL -
       [http://www.slideshare.net/CassEveritt/approaching-zero-driver-over
       head]Slides -
       [https://www.reddit.com/r/gamedev/comments/21mbo8/we_are_the_author
       s_of_approaching_zero_driver]AMA Reddit by Cass Everitt, Tim Foley,
       John McDonald, Graham Sellers [1:15:54]
     * [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=-bCeNzgiJ8I]How Modern OpenGL Can
       Radically Reduce Driver Overhead by Cass Everitt, John McDonald
       [51:13]
     * [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=45O7WTc6k2Y]Moving Your Games to
       OpenGL by Rich Geldreich, Dan Ginsburg, Peter Lohrmann, Jason
       Mitchell [54:45]

Videos

   OpenGL video tutorials
     * [https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLbLaohICnSGUx0zZ4ffxEzQvWEz
       xWH839]CodeAcademy - Several tutorial videos about modern OpenGL
       and rendering techniques.
     * [https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLRwVmtr-pp06qT6ckboaOhnm9Fx
       mzHpbY]Jamie King - Compreheensive tutorials about modern OpenGL
       and Qt.
     * [https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLSPw4ASQYyymu3PfG9gxywSPghn
       SMiOAW]MakingGamesWithBen - Video tutorials (step-by-step) about
       OpenGL and game development.
     * [https://www.youtube.com/user/ACMSIGGRAPH/playlists]SIGGRAPH -
       Popular conference about computer graphics.
     * [https://www.youtube.com/user/thebennybox/playlists]thebennybox -
       Videos tutorials about OpenGL and game development.
     * [https://www.youtube.com/user/ThinMatrix/playlists]ThinMatrix -
       Video tutorials about OpenGL and game development using Java.
     * [https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLQVvvaa0QuDdfGpqjkEJSeWKGCP
       31__wD]sentdex - Videos tutorials about OpenGL (immediate mode)
       using Python.
     * [https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLRtjMdoYXLf6zUMDJVRZYV-6g6n
       62vet8]Sonar Systems - Learn about the new and modern OpenGL 3.0+.

